      <symbol type="16" id="90" code="412" name="Cultivated land">
        <description>Cultivated land, normally used for growing crops. Runnability may vary according to the type of crops grown and the time of year. Since the runnability may vary, such areas should be avoided when setting courses.
The symbol is combined with symbol Out-of-bounds area (709) to show cultivated land that shall not be entered.
Minimum width: 3 mm.
Minimum area: 9 mm² (144 m²).</description>
        <combined_symbol parts="2">
          <part symbol="70" />
          <part symbol="91" />
        </combined_symbol>
      </symbol>
